You haven't drunk all night.

20:03.379 --> 20:04.586
I am drinking.

20:04.655 --> 20:06.413
Ah, but not in the game.

20:06.482 --> 20:08.310
That's because
I'm not playing.

20:08.379 --> 20:09.586
You set down to play.

20:10.655 --> 20:13.206
Shh.

20:16.827 --> 20:18.379
Come on, Aaron.

20:18.448 --> 20:19.586
If she doesn't want to
drink, don't make her drink.

20:19.655 --> 20:20.655
No.

20:20.724 --> 20:22.068
Not everyone-- no drama.

20:22.137 --> 20:23.620
You want in?
All in.

20:23.689 --> 20:24.655
OK.

20:24.724 --> 20:26.206
New game.
Yeah!

20:26.275 --> 20:27.793
Whoa.

20:27.862 --> 20:31.172
the new game is, who's
most likely to, so who's--

20:31.241 --> 20:34.103
who's most likely
to be a virgin and--

20:34.172 --> 20:36.413
Heinrich!

20:36.482 --> 20:38.206
Who's most likely to lose?

20:38.275 --> 20:39.310
Heinrich!

20:39.379 --> 20:40.413
Ah!
Show us, show us.

20:40.482 --> 20:41.448
Heinrich!

20:41.517 --> 20:42.793
Take it off!

20:42.862 --> 20:44.517
- Take it off!
- Come on.

20:44.586 --> 20:45.931
Come on, Heinrich.

20:46.000 --> 20:47.896
- Rock the boat!
- Rock the boat!

20:47.965 --> 20:49.517
Oh, look at that body.

21:10.379 --> 21:13.586
♪ Sometimes
you love too hard ♪

21:13.655 --> 21:15.551
♪ Sometimes you go too far ♪

21:15.620 --> 21:18.965
Oh my God.

21:19.034 --> 21:21.379
♪ Real things
do not come easy ♪

21:21.448 --> 21:23.344
♪ Never been
your average girl ♪

21:23.413 --> 21:26.344
♪ So take time with me,
take time ♪

21:26.413 --> 21:29.275
♪ Baby, talk to me
with some action ♪

21:29.344 --> 21:32.000
♪ We can find a place
for your passion ♪

21:32.068 --> 21:33.551
♪ Cool down, simmer ♪

21:45.000 --> 21:46.931
♪ Cool down, simmer ♪

22:08.862 --> 22:10.206
♪ Cool down, simmer ♪

22:10.275 --> 22:11.758
♪ Cool down, please me ♪

22:11.827 --> 22:12.724
♪ Cool down, simmer ♪

22:12.793 --> 22:13.724
♪ Cool down ♪

22:19.413 --> 22:21.482
♪ Boy, you make it too
hard for me to stay here ♪

22:21.551 --> 22:24.655
♪ Boy, you're making it hard
for me to be your love ♪

23:19.758 --> 23:21.896
Need something?

23:23.896 --> 23:25.172
No.

23:25.241 --> 23:26.758
No, I was just
looking for the loo.

23:26.827 --> 23:30.517
Well, do you think
it's in my cabin?

23:34.517 --> 23:36.413
Well, come.
I'll show you something.

23:49.965 --> 23:53.344
How come you get a free
pass on all the games?

23:53.413 --> 23:54.379
Not free.

23:54.448 --> 23:57.862
Believe me, I pay.

23:57.931 --> 23:59.758
What's that?

23:59.827 --> 24:02.517
Absinthe.

24:04.517 --> 24:06.413
Is it going to make me
trip out or something?

24:07.448 --> 24:08.931
No.

24:09.000 --> 24:10.827
It's just a myth.

24:10.896 --> 24:13.241
It's just alcohol.

24:14.137 --> 24:16.655
That's a lot of fuss
if it's just booze?

24:16.724 --> 24:22.862
Well, I like fuss.

24:29.517 --> 24:31.241
Did you paint that?

24:37.896 --> 24:39.551
Every boat needs an artist.

24:41.655 --> 24:42.724
Are you Filipino?

24:42.793 --> 24:46.793
Uh, my-- my dad is Filipino.

24:46.862 --> 24:49.068
And my mom is French.

24:51.448 --> 24:54.931
But back home in
France, I'm Asian,

24:55.000 --> 24:57.103
and here in Asia, I'm French.

24:57.172 --> 24:59.275
I don't know, so you tell me.

25:04.551 --> 25:07.172
You're all from
different countries then?

25:09.724 --> 25:11.275
She's Aaron's boat.

25:11.344 --> 25:13.068
The rest of us-- we joined
from different places,

25:13.137 --> 25:16.241
people he meets along the way.

25:18.137 --> 25:20.965
How old are you?

25:21.034 --> 25:22.793
25.

25:22.862 --> 25:25.137
Bullshit.

25:25.206 --> 25:26.965
You're bullshit.

25:28.482 --> 25:31.206
Well, English girls
who travel this way,

25:31.275 --> 25:33.275
most go straight to Phuket,

25:33.344 --> 25:35.896
get fucked up
at the Full Moon Party.

25:35.965 --> 25:38.793
Yet you're in the Philippines.

25:38.862 --> 25:40.241
Why?

25:43.551 --> 25:46.413
I don't know.

25:46.482 --> 25:47.931
Why are you?

25:48.000 --> 25:51.689
I'm running away.

25:51.758 --> 25:53.310
Aren't we all?

26:03.034 --> 26:09.000
Mm. Oh, fuck.

26:09.068 --> 26:12.793
♪ All that I wanted, yeah ♪

26:38.517 --> 26:41.448
Ugh.

26:52.310 --> 26:53.482
Kit.
Kitty.

26:53.551 --> 26:54.482
Oh!

26:54.551 --> 26:56.448
Sorry.

26:56.517 --> 26:58.137
Fuck.

26:58.206 --> 26:59.620
We sailed off.

26:59.689 --> 27:01.000
What?

27:01.068 --> 27:02.655
We're in the
middle of the sea.

27:07.172 --> 27:10.931
I don't even remember
falling asleep.

27:11.000 --> 27:13.275
God, where the fuck are we?

27:32.172 --> 27:35.241
- Stop.
- Sorry, where are we?

27:35.310 --> 27:37.827
On our way to
beautiful Mindanao.

27:37.896 --> 27:40.241
Hope that's OK.

27:40.310 --> 27:42.241
Yeah, that's great.

27:42.310 --> 27:45.275
Yeah, we got a stop off
in Balakid first, pick up

27:45.344 --> 27:46.793
some supplies for New Year's.

27:46.862 --> 27:48.448
Then we're going to head
down the coast a bit,

27:48.517 --> 27:50.034
do a bit of island-hopping.

27:50.103 --> 27:51.655
I'm sure young
Joseph here would

27:51.724 --> 27:53.931
be happy to drop in town.

27:54.000 --> 27:57.517
Or you could just stay on.

27:57.586 --> 27:58.517
Wait.

27:58.586 --> 27:59.724
What?

27:59.793 --> 28:01.275
Do you mean go on
island hopping with you?

28:01.344 --> 28:03.000
Call it our way
of saying thank you for

28:03.068 --> 28:04.862
returning the wallet.

28:10.517 --> 28:13.482
So is that a yes?

28:16.379 --> 28:17.827
Yeah.

28:17.896 --> 28:20.655
- Great.
- Great.

28:20.724 --> 28:22.793
- Yeah?
- Yeah. Sounds good.

28:32.068 --> 28:33.068
Yeah.

28:36.689 --> 28:39.206
There are a few
rules on this boat, OK?

28:39.275 --> 28:41.931
On "The Blue," everything
is held collectively.

28:42.000 --> 28:44.482
All work is shared,
and we all contribute equally.

28:44.551 --> 28:45.793
OK?

28:45.862 --> 28:50.862
That means $50 a week
each for expenses.

28:50.931 --> 28:52.034
Yeah, that sounds fair.

28:52.103 --> 28:53.310
All right.

28:53.379 --> 28:55.172
This will be you.

28:55.241 --> 28:58.034
Mm, it's nice.

28:58.103 --> 29:04.344
Yeah, she's a great old
boat, a little bit creaky.

29:04.413 --> 29:07.448
She leaves a small wake.

29:07.517 --> 29:09.137
You sail on her, I expect
you to do the same.

29:09.206 --> 29:10.689
OK?
We don't waste.

29:10.758 --> 29:11.551
We don't pollute.

29:11.620 --> 29:13.655
And we do not exploit.

29:13.724 --> 29:15.931
That was totally
our philosophy.

29:18.034 --> 29:19.413
OK.

29:19.482 --> 29:23.310
Secondly, all decisions
are made by via a vote.

29:23.379 --> 29:24.793
Except when safety's concerned.

29:24.862 --> 29:26.137
Then I'm in charge,
no questions asked.

29:26.206 --> 29:27.448
Yeah.

29:27.517 --> 29:28.862
I mean,
it's your boat, so sure.

29:28.931 --> 29:29.931
Yeah.

29:30.000 --> 29:31.586
Lastly, and the most important.

29:31.655 --> 29:32.931
No sex on board.

29:33.000 --> 29:34.413
All right?

29:34.482 --> 29:35.724
You want to screw,
you find someone on shore.

29:37.310 --> 29:39.896
Because my crew do not
screw, at least not each other.

29:42.620 --> 29:44.862
Lana?

29:44.931 --> 29:46.586
That's fine.

29:46.655 --> 29:47.620
Good.

29:47.689 --> 29:49.241
OK, well, settle yourselves in.

29:49.310 --> 29:50.689
Dinner's at six.

29:50.758 --> 29:52.310
Thank you.

29:52.379 --> 29:53.931
Treat my boat right, OK?

29:54.000 --> 29:55.758
Don't waste freshwater.

29:55.827 --> 29:57.689
I'll stay happy.

29:57.758 --> 29:58.896
Enjoy.

30:00.448 --> 30:02.103
- Did you see--
- Get off.

30:02.172 --> 30:04.206
Did you see
he's got a ring on his finger?

30:04.275 --> 30:06.000
Yeah, because he's married.

30:06.068 --> 30:07.344
He's a married man.

30:08.931 --> 30:10.758
Where's is his wife then?

30:10.827 --> 30:13.000
Kit, put it away.

30:13.068 --> 30:16.379
Apparently there were
signs of trouble on board,

30:16.448 --> 30:17.965
a fight maybe.

30:18.034 --> 30:21.620
Can you think of anything
that may have caused that?

30:21.689 --> 30:23.724
- Like what?
- I don't know.

30:23.793 --> 30:25.206
I wasn't there.

30:25.275 --> 30:26.896
Maybe something
didn't feel right,

30:26.965 --> 30:29.758
something someone said or did.

30:32.310 --> 30:33.482
Listen, Emma.

30:33.551 --> 30:35.034
If the crew are
in the water, they

30:35.103 --> 30:37.482
have a maximum of 48
hours before they succumb

30:37.551 --> 30:39.275
to hypothermia,
so if there's anything

30:39.344 --> 30:40.724
that you can think of--

30:40.793 --> 30:42.758
I don't know what you
want me to tell you.

30:42.827 --> 30:46.413
They were just a bunch of
travelers having a laugh.

30:55.172 --> 30:57.586
I've put some money away
to cover a week on the boat.

30:57.655 --> 31:01.275
That should get us clothes,
swimsuits, seasick meds.

31:01.344 --> 31:03.000
Won't that leave
us skint again?

31:03.068 --> 31:05.103
I can't keep wearing this.

31:05.172 --> 31:06.862
We're on Mindanao, OK?

31:06.931 --> 31:10.034
We can save the money, get away
tonight before they get back.

31:10.103 --> 31:11.482
No, no.

31:11.551 --> 31:13.172
Lan, on that boat we're
completely off the grid.

31:13.241 --> 31:14.137
For like a week.

31:15.655 --> 31:16.689
Yeah, in a week we'll
be way down south,

31:16.758 --> 31:18.413
like hundreds of
miles from here.

31:18.482 --> 31:20.172
Don't we need a proper plan,

31:20.241 --> 31:21.827
like for what
happens after that?

31:21.896 --> 31:23.551
Ugh, why?

31:23.620 --> 31:25.827
Sooner or later we're
going to get caught.

31:25.896 --> 31:27.931
With no money,
it's probably sooner.

31:28.000 --> 31:29.000
No.

31:29.068 --> 31:30.586
I won't let that happen.

31:30.655 --> 31:34.586
I know, but island-hopping
through Southeast Asia

31:34.655 --> 31:36.689
on a private bloody
yacht-- that's like

31:36.758 --> 31:39.724
someone else's like life,
someone much luckier than us.

31:39.793 --> 31:41.379
I want to enjoy it
while we can.

31:41.448 --> 31:44.241
Please.
Please.

31:53.827 --> 31:57.137
both: Woo!

31:57.206 --> 31:58.241
Woo!

32:08.103 --> 32:09.172
It's over there.

32:19.689 --> 32:23.517
OK, so you can grab the meds.

32:23.586 --> 32:25.000
Maybe I'll get us
some new clothes,

32:25.068 --> 32:28.000
and then we can meet back
here in 30 minutes?

32:28.068 --> 32:29.275
Cool.

32:29.344 --> 32:30.586
Are you listening to me?

32:30.655 --> 32:31.620
Yes, I am listening.

32:31.689 --> 32:33.034
OK.

32:33.103 --> 32:34.275
See you in a bit.

32:34.344 --> 32:35.310
Bye.

32:35.379 --> 32:37.965
Be safe.

34:12.448 --> 34:15.068
Lana.

34:15.137 --> 34:16.379
Denny.

34:16.448 --> 34:18.275
Here.

34:18.344 --> 34:19.413
Hey, what's up?

34:20.758 --> 34:21.724
The police were shooting
back there.

34:21.793 --> 34:22.862
I don't know what's going on.

34:22.931 --> 34:23.758
Yeah, I heard.

34:23.827 --> 34:25.034
We better get out of here.

34:25.103 --> 34:26.620
- I need to find Kitty.
- Hey, hey.

34:26.689 --> 34:28.206
She would have gone
back to the boat.

34:28.275 --> 34:29.793
What if she hasn't?
What if she's gotten lost?

34:29.862 --> 34:30.862
Then I'll go out
myself and find her.

34:30.931 --> 34:32.206
I promise.

34:32.275 --> 34:33.275
But those cops aren't
good people, so we've

34:33.344 --> 34:37.000
really got to move now.

34:42.068 --> 34:45.586
So were you just meeting up
with an old mate back there?

34:45.655 --> 34:48.965
Yeah, kind of.

34:49.034 --> 34:49.965
All right.

34:50.034 --> 34:51.793
I was picking up a bit of weed.

34:51.862 --> 34:53.655
Sometimes when my shift
ends it's hard to wind down,

34:53.724 --> 34:55.103
and a smoke helps.

34:55.172 --> 34:56.172
But--

34:56.241 --> 34:57.241
Aaron wouldn't like that.

34:57.310 --> 34:59.310
This way.

34:59.379 --> 35:00.482
Particularly not from me.

35:00.551 --> 35:03.103
From me, he expects more.

35:05.793 --> 35:07.310
It's just a big
brother thing, I guess,

35:07.379 --> 35:09.793
a bit like you and Kitty.

35:09.862 --> 35:10.931
She's not my big sister.

35:11.000 --> 35:12.206
Yeah, but she acts it, right?

35:12.275 --> 35:15.586
Like she's always in charge?

35:15.655 --> 35:16.793
It's not like that.

35:16.862 --> 35:18.241
Hey, look, I get it.

35:18.310 --> 35:19.931
You two are close,
just like me and Aaron.

35:20.000 --> 35:21.655
But sometimes you got
to do your own thing,

35:21.724 --> 35:23.586
you know, at bit of
time on your own.

35:23.655 --> 35:25.068
Yeah.

35:25.137 --> 35:28.241
Don't worry, I'm not
going to grass you up.

35:28.310 --> 35:31.689
Never thought you would.

35:31.758 --> 35:33.137
By the way, those earrings--

35:33.206 --> 35:34.344
I feel like I've seen
them somewhere before.

35:35.827 --> 35:37.034
Yeah, I-- I was going
to give them back.

35:37.103 --> 35:38.655
I was just borrowing them.
Don't worry.

35:38.724 --> 35:41.793
I don't grass either.

35:53.931 --> 35:56.275
I thought you'd been shot.

35:56.344 --> 35:59.275
And if you weren't shot,
you know, you'd be lost.

35:59.344 --> 36:00.344
I was.

36:00.413 --> 36:01.482
Denny found me.

36:01.551 --> 36:03.379
Well, hooray for the Denny.

36:03.448 --> 36:04.724
All right.

36:04.793 --> 36:05.896
I'm on dinner
shift, so unless you

36:05.965 --> 36:07.206
want to see Aaron
blow a circuit,

36:07.275 --> 36:08.586
we've got to get back.

36:08.655 --> 36:10.103
I just blown away by how
you guys get around.

36:10.172 --> 36:12.344
I always look like a
dumb, dumbass tourist.

36:12.413 --> 36:14.551
You are
a dumbass tourist.

36:14.620 --> 36:19.103
That was rude.

36:19.172 --> 36:22.413
So what did you guys get up to?

36:22.482 --> 36:23.482
- Today?
- Yeah.

36:55.137 --> 36:57.551
Ahh!

37:09.620 --> 37:10.620
Hello.

37:10.689 --> 37:12.310
Are you all right?

37:12.379 --> 37:16.241
Thank you.

37:19.103 --> 37:23.103
Sometimes I-- I wonder
why I stay on this boat.

37:28.137 --> 37:31.724
Then I see a view
like this, and I know.

37:36.034 --> 37:38.068
Lana, hey, Aaron
wants me to give you

37:38.137 --> 37:40.241
a lesson in helming the boat.

37:41.724 --> 37:43.896
Like steering it?

37:43.965 --> 37:46.172
It'll be painless.

37:46.241 --> 37:50.413
Come on.

37:55.241 --> 37:57.103
All right.

37:57.172 --> 37:58.793
You ready?

37:58.862 --> 38:02.620
First you flick that.

38:02.689 --> 38:03.793
- Should I do it?
- Yeah.

38:03.862 --> 38:04.793
Engine on.

38:06.310 --> 38:08.655
Let it warm up.

38:08.724 --> 38:11.689
Very good.

38:11.758 --> 38:14.758
You want to honk the horn?

38:14.827 --> 38:16.275
Go on.

38:16.344 --> 38:17.862
OK.

38:19.482 --> 38:22.413
A bit longer.

38:23.931 --> 38:27.620
Perfect.
All right, now put into gear.

38:27.689 --> 38:29.965
- OK.
- You see where we are?

38:30.034 --> 38:32.103
♪ Why is it so ♪

38:32.172 --> 38:33.724
OK, ocean navigation
for dummies.

38:33.793 --> 38:35.448
So right now,
it's on autopilot,

38:35.517 --> 38:37.241
so there's not much to do.

38:37.310 --> 38:40.793
But I'm going to turn that off
and give you a feel for it.

38:40.862 --> 38:43.172
Yeah, but what if I crash?

38:43.241 --> 38:45.413
Into what?

38:45.482 --> 38:46.689
You ready?

38:46.758 --> 38:48.448
- Yeah.
- It's off.

38:48.517 --> 38:49.482
You got it?

38:49.551 --> 38:51.724
Quick. Quick.

38:51.793 --> 38:53.241
- OK.
- All right.

38:53.310 --> 38:58.000
So first thing-- she steers a
lot slower than a car.

38:58.068 --> 38:59.689
I don't know how to
drive a car either.

38:59.758 --> 39:01.206
Oh, great.

39:01.275 --> 39:02.862
You don't have any
bad habits to unlearn.

39:02.931 --> 39:04.068
Keep your eye on the island.

39:04.137 --> 39:07.931
♪ Why is it so rotten? ♪

39:09.862 --> 39:12.517
Left.

39:12.586 --> 39:14.551
Yeah, you've got it.

39:14.620 --> 39:15.620
Go ahead.
Go ahead.

39:15.689 --> 39:17.103
Ooh,
it's pulling to the left.

39:17.172 --> 39:19.965
♪ Straight to
the heart with a toy ♪

39:20.034 --> 39:22.724
Spin, spin, spin.

39:22.793 --> 39:23.724
That's it.

39:23.793 --> 39:25.379
It's not a car.

39:25.448 --> 39:27.551
It's nothing like a car,

39:27.620 --> 39:29.896
especially this boat.

39:29.965 --> 39:31.724
All right.
Now we're good.

39:31.793 --> 39:32.896
You're just going to go left.

39:38.724 --> 39:40.344
All right, we're straight.

39:44.172 --> 39:45.827
Do you get signal out here?

39:45.896 --> 39:47.517
A couple of bars.

39:47.586 --> 39:48.551
There's a town over there.

39:54.000 --> 39:55.241
Do you want another drink?

39:55.310 --> 39:56.310
I'm good.

39:56.379 --> 39:57.344
Yeah?

39:57.413 --> 40:00.000
- No.
- OK.

40:56.448 --> 40:59.310
So, Joseph, your
family's religious then?

40:59.379 --> 41:05.034
My father is Catholic, very
Catholic, like many Filipinos.

41:05.103 --> 41:07.655
Before the church came here,
people

41:07.724 --> 41:09.931
used to worship spirits.

41:10.000 --> 41:11.068
Spirits?

41:11.137 --> 41:13.241
Like, what, ghosts?

41:13.310 --> 41:16.068
More like nature gods,
but there is

41:16.137 --> 41:18.655
one island on that coast
that was meant to be

41:18.724 --> 41:20.896
a bridge to the afterlife.

41:20.965 --> 41:22.448
Dayang?

41:24.310 --> 41:28.000
I went out there once
with this local guy.

41:28.068 --> 41:30.344
He wouldn't even
get off the boat.

41:30.413 --> 41:31.689
I did.

41:31.758 --> 41:34.137
But he warned me not
to bring anything back

41:34.206 --> 41:36.827
or I might take
the curse with me.

41:36.896 --> 41:38.931
Did you bring anything back?

41:39.965 --> 41:45.103
A beautiful conch too
irresistible to leave behind.

41:45.172 --> 41:46.620
Where's the conch now?

41:46.689 --> 41:48.517
I gave it to
Heinrich for Christmas,

41:48.586 --> 41:51.862
but I don't think it's
really affected him at all.

41:53.862 --> 41:55.724
- Oh!
- Ah!

41:57.586 --> 41:58.517
Whew!

41:58.586 --> 41:59.620
OK.

41:59.689 --> 42:01.689
So evil and unnecessary.

42:01.758 --> 42:06.551
All right, so you
now give it a spin.

42:06.620 --> 42:07.655
And--

42:07.724 --> 42:09.827
Den, where are we, mate?

42:09.896 --> 42:10.931
Oh, shit, sorry.

42:11.000 --> 42:12.689
I was giving Lana a lesson.

42:12.758 --> 42:14.275
We might have strayed a bit.

42:14.344 --> 42:15.896
A bit?

42:15.965 --> 42:17.413
We've gone out, out, out, out.
Sorry.

42:17.482 --> 42:18.758
Sorry.

42:18.827 --> 42:19.862
Look, we're 45 degrees
off the course I set.

42:19.931 --> 42:20.896
Come on.

42:20.965 --> 42:22.413
How do I know?

42:22.482 --> 42:27.103
Jesus.

42:27.172 --> 42:30.379
Guys, there's a
weird light over there.

42:41.275 --> 42:43.517
Funny flash pattern.

42:43.586 --> 42:45.034
What does that mean?

42:45.103 --> 42:46.137
A light flashing in
a particular sequence

42:46.206 --> 42:47.241
can be a message.

42:47.310 --> 42:49.724
Emergency signal, for instance.

42:53.655 --> 42:55.931
Better check it out.

43:09.689 --> 43:12.137
Trawler, trawler,
this is yacht "The Blue."

43:12.206 --> 43:13.344
Do you copy?

43:13.413 --> 43:14.862
Over.

43:14.931 --> 43:17.965
Trawler, trawler, trawler,
this is yacht "The Blue."

43:18.034 --> 43:18.931
Do you copy?

43:19.000 --> 43:20.689
Over.

43:20.758 --> 43:22.517
Hey!
Hey!

43:23.931 --> 43:24.931
Do you copy?

43:26.103 --> 43:28.034
Over.

43:31.655 --> 43:33.931
Hey!

43:34.000 --> 43:36.655
No response, Chelle?

43:36.724 --> 43:38.137
Do you see anyone?

43:38.206 --> 43:39.172
Why would it just
be sitting out here

43:39.241 --> 43:40.344
in the middle of nowhere?

43:40.413 --> 43:41.655
Hey!

43:41.724 --> 43:43.896
Maybe it was towed
there or something.

43:43.965 --> 43:45.758
- Why would they do that?
- No idea.

43:45.827 --> 43:46.896
Your guess is as good as mine.

43:46.965 --> 43:49.206
Let's take a look.

43:49.275 --> 43:51.344
Denny, is it-- what--

43:51.413 --> 43:53.034
oh my God.
You're insane.

43:53.103 --> 43:54.137
What--

43:54.206 --> 43:56.103
- Hey!
- What are you doing?

43:58.620 --> 44:00.172
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

44:02.758 --> 44:05.034
Den-Den, what the
fuck are you doing?

44:05.103 --> 44:07.517
Taking a look.

44:11.172 --> 44:13.137
They're insane.

44:13.206 --> 44:14.620
What if there's sharks
or-- or jellyfish?

44:14.689 --> 44:16.413
Wait, wait.
What are you doing?

44:16.482 --> 44:17.793
Lana?

44:17.862 --> 44:20.655
Lana!

44:20.724 --> 44:23.758
Lana, what are you doing?

44:23.827 --> 44:25.965
I wanna see what's going on.

44:26.034 --> 44:27.724
Why?

45:41.586 --> 45:42.517
Denny?

45:42.586 --> 45:44.793
Heinrich?

46:02.551 --> 46:05.034
Hey.

46:05.103 --> 46:06.655
What did you find?

46:10.137 --> 46:11.448
Lana.

46:37.862 --> 46:39.344
Help them up, Michelle.

47:01.241 --> 47:04.758
What's going on?

47:24.551 --> 47:26.517
What the fuck is this?

47:26.586 --> 47:28.689
Is that even real?

47:28.758 --> 47:30.241
Rick found it one
of the deck lockers.

47:30.310 --> 47:32.413
Yeah, so what?

47:32.482 --> 47:34.586
So you just took it?

47:34.655 --> 47:36.551
Well, couldn't leave it.

47:36.620 --> 47:38.655
Yeah.
Yeah, you could.

47:41.103 --> 47:43.103
Skipper, that boat
is completely empty.

47:43.172 --> 47:44.689
I mean, there's like not
even the engine inside.

47:44.758 --> 47:46.068
He's right.

47:46.137 --> 47:47.172
It looks like it's been
that way for years.

47:47.241 --> 47:48.137
- Really?
- Yes.

47:48.206 --> 47:49.275
Really?

47:49.344 --> 47:50.172
So what's with the
flashing lights?

47:50.241 --> 47:51.379
You guys.

47:51.448 --> 47:52.379
Aaron, this--
this isn't right.

47:52.448 --> 47:53.620
That's--
Guys, shut up.

47:53.689 --> 47:55.482
I think there's a
boat coming this way.

48:00.103 --> 48:01.896
We got to put that
bag back right now.

48:01.965 --> 48:03.448
Chelle, by the
time we swim across

48:03.517 --> 48:05.068
that boat will be on us.

48:05.137 --> 48:06.517
We should just leave.

48:06.586 --> 48:07.551
I mean, they probably
can't even see us.

48:07.620 --> 48:08.517
We've got to leave now.

48:08.586 --> 48:10.241
No, this is crazy.

48:10.310 --> 48:11.413
We don't know
who's on that boat.

48:11.482 --> 48:12.931
So what?

48:13.000 --> 48:15.000
You just want to hang
around and find out?

48:21.137 --> 48:25.655
Aaron, make a call.

48:25.724 --> 48:27.896
All right. Turn all
the fucking lights off.

48:27.965 --> 48:29.068
Let's get out of here.

48:29.137 --> 48:30.241
Aaron.

48:30.310 --> 48:32.344
Turn the fucking lights out.

48:32.413 --> 48:35.068
Figure it out later.

48:48.551 --> 48:50.068
Well, we needed money.

48:50.137 --> 48:53.827
Maybe everything's
going to be all right.

48:53.896 --> 48:56.758
It will be.

49:02.000 --> 49:03.068
All right.

49:03.137 --> 49:04.896
We're going to have
to wind this up.

49:04.965 --> 49:06.862
Before we do, there's
something I'd like you to hear.

49:08.965 --> 49:09.931
Hello?

49:10.000 --> 49:11.206
Can you hear me?

49:11.275 --> 49:13.448
"The Blue." "The Blue."
We need you!

49:13.517 --> 49:15.000
Help!

49:15.068 --> 49:16.896
"MOL Triumph" to "The Blue,"
reading you.

49:16.965 --> 49:18.448
We're in trouble.
Help me.

49:18.517 --> 49:19.482
Can you hear me?

49:19.551 --> 49:20.827
Fuck, can you hear me?

49:20.896 --> 49:22.517
Blue, we are
attempting to respond

49:22.586 --> 49:23.896
to your distress signal.

49:23.965 --> 49:25.620
Are you able to
give your position?

49:25.689 --> 49:27.344
I-- I don't know.

49:27.413 --> 49:28.793
I don't know where.

49:28.862 --> 49:30.034
Oh God.

49:30.103 --> 49:32.103
I-- I-- I don't
know where we are.

49:32.172 --> 49:33.551
Think.
Oh God.

49:33.620 --> 49:36.517
He's dead.
He's dead!

49:36.586 --> 49:39.793
It's just static after that.

49:39.862 --> 49:44.241
That's the recording of the
distress signal I mentioned.

49:44.310 --> 49:47.655
You recognize the voice?

49:48.586 --> 49:50.068
This crew list--

49:50.137 --> 49:54.379
the only woman on it is
Michelle Wilson, American.

49:54.448 --> 49:57.620
It's not Chelle.

49:59.896 --> 50:02.068
Any idea who
it might be then?

50:05.241 --> 50:08.896
No.

50:08.965 --> 50:11.862
I've never heard
that voice before.

50:17.137 --> 50:18.103
All right.

50:18.172 --> 50:22.413
Well, thanks, Emma.

50:22.482 --> 50:24.827
You've been a big help.

50:36.275 --> 50:39.137
Thanks for your time, Emma.

51:04.517 --> 51:05.965
You have rung Kitty.

51:06.034 --> 51:08.862
Did you really
expect me to pick up?

51:08.931 --> 51:12.137
Leave me a message,
and I will call you back.

51:12.206 --> 51:16.034
Kit, I know you
probably won't get this,

51:16.103 --> 51:20.551
but I'm scared.

51:20.620 --> 51:21.620
I'm sorry.

51:21.689 --> 51:22.965
I'm sorry for what I did.

51:23.034 --> 51:25.931
I'm really sorry.

51:43.310 --> 51:47.655
SAR to command,
we spotted something.

51:48.551 --> 51:51.586
We have a body.
